tweet: Building trust is a long and complicated process. Trust requires communication, collaboration, cooperation, openness, respect, understanding, and performance.  Can the government deliver on trust?  #KisanAandolan
name: Sam Pitroda

tweet: Government promises & performance is visible to the farmers. They know that their income did not increase as promised, and jobs were not created for their young.  They are disappointed that the rich became more prosperous and the poor remained poor.#KisanAandolan
name: Sam Pitroda

tweet: To me, protesting farmers are saying loud and clear, “We have lost trust in the government. They do not mean what they say and do not say what they mean”.  Farmers want the truth, trust, and justice. #KisanAandolan
name: Sam Pitroda

tweet: Large numbers of farmers are now around Delhi in the bitter cold without adequate facilities to show solidarity and support. #KisanAandolan
name: Sam Pitroda

tweet: It is heartbreaking to watch what is happening to the protesting farmers in India. They are demonstrating against the three Farm bills passed by the Indian Parliament.  #KisanAandolan
